Ten moles of an ideal gas are compressed isothermally and reversibly from a pressure of 1 atm to 10 atm at 300 K. Which of the following statements correctly evaluates the work $W$ done *on* the gas during this compression, and during its reverse process (isothermal expansion)?

#set page(width: a_width, height: auto, margin: a_margin)
#set text(size: a_size)
$W = +57.4 " kJ"$ during compression, and $W = -57.4 " kJ"$ during the reverse expansion.
#pagebreak()
$W = -57.4 " kJ"$ during compression, and $W = +57.4 " kJ"$ during the reverse expansion.
#pagebreak()
$W = +57.4 " kJ"$ during compression, and $W = 0 " kJ"$ during the reverse expansion.
#pagebreak()
$W = -57.4 " kJ"$ during compression, and $W = -57.4 " kJ"$ during the reverse expansion.

